oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Galilee Primitive Baptist Church: auxiliary building
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: West, Carroll Van, photographer
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Color photograph of concrete block, gable-front auxiliary building located next to the church. A central set of steps lead to the screened front door. A pair of windows flank the front door. Three windows, one containing an air-conditioning unit, appear on the side of the building.

Galilee Primitive Baptist Church's current building replaced an earlier church dating from 1940. The previous building [pictured] was a concrete-block, gable-front church. At the time of fieldwork, Robert S. Evenson served as pastor and the church was deemed potentially eligible for the National Register.
